DATA CLOUD
Connect Data

To get started with Data Cloud, you connect a data source, through either data federation or data ingestion. Data federation sets up direct connectivity with data sources. It uses a Zero-ETL integration that eliminates the need to copy data into Data Cloud. During data ingestion, data is brought into Data Cloud in its original form and stored in a data lake object (DLO).

Connectors

You can connect data sources, such as Amazon S3, Marketing Cloud Engagement, and Google Storage, to Data Cloud using a dedicated connector. Select the data source connector that you want to import data from, and then indicate the object or dataset that you want to federate with or ingest. Data Cloud retrieves a sample of your data and provides a recommended source schema for your review.

Data Streams

A data stream uses a connector to establish a connection with a data source. A data stream acts as a pipeline for connecting data to Data Cloud. The ingested data is organized into a schema and stored as data lake objects (DLOs).

When creating a data stream, you specify the category and optionally the event time, primary key, and organization unit identifier. You can enhance your data using formula fields to clean and adjust raw data. You can also configure the scheduling details to manage how often data is refreshed.

Data Object Concepts and Schema in Data Cloud
During ingestion, Data Cloud retrieves a sample of your data and recommends a source schema. You can then review and modify the recommended schema.
Data Sources in Data Cloud
Data sources are ingested into or connected to Data Cloud in different ways with specific requirements and steps that an admin configures before creating a data stream.
Data Streams in Data Cloud
Data streams are the connections and associated data ingested into Data Cloud.
Connect Unstructured Data to Data Cloud
After you create a connection between a data source and Data Cloud, you can reference unstructured data from external blob stores in Data Cloud by creating an unstructured data lake object and mapping it to an unstructured data model object.
